[30;1m463 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m464 | [0m[35m* In order to achieve interoperability with existing software 'in the wild',[0m
[30;1m465 | [0m[35m  suds does not fully conform to the WSDL 1.1 specification with regard as to[0m

[30;1m42 | [0m[35mIf an input parameter is represented by structured XSD element containing other[0m

[30;1m44 | [0m[35mconsidered ``wrapped``, then suds library's web service operation invocation[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35mfunction will take values for the input parameter's internal elements as input[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35marguments, instead of taking only a single wrapper object as a value for the[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35mexternal wrapper element.[0m

[30;1m29 | [0m[35mBare/wrapped web service operation input parameters[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m===================================================[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35mWhen suds library models a web service operation, it can be configured to map[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35meach of its message parts to a single input parameter expecting values directly[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35mmatching the data type defined for that message part in the web service's WSDL[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35mschema. Such input parameters are called ``bare``.[0m

[30;1m41 | [0m[35m        return env[0m
